pulltitle: Get some unit tests running again
pullsbody:
This works by adding explicit dependencies for a bunch of stuff into karma.conf.js so that it actually gets loaded. This takes us from 21/21 tests failing to 17/21 failing.

So, forward progress.  There is probably a better fix for this that avoids duplicating test config data, but just getting the unit tests running at all seems like a higher priority.

Also removed the karma-e2e.conf.js file, since it's unused and as such just serves to confuse new developers.
pull_repo_desc: [deprecated] a kanban board integrated with bugzilla
pull_commit_message: Unbreak some of the tests by making karma load all the dependencies

pullsbody: Pin a bunch of the version dependencies so that things start to work again.  Among other things, angular-bootstrap 0.6.0 broke backwards compatibility in at least one big way, so we need to pin to earlier than that.  Also cleanup some documentation so it's easier for a new dev to get started.
